div1.p:
Pace. I served the subpoena on the landlord personally in the samehouse;
Mary Clark
was with me.

EDWARD LAWLER
. Q. Do you know any thing about this - A. Yes; I saw
Elizabeth Clark
on the 23rd of November, about six o'clock in the evening;
Elizabeth Clark
was picking the putty off Mr. Audley's shop-window;
Jack Sweeney
stood by her;
Elizabeth Clark
took the glass out of the window. I saw her put her hand into the shop window; she took out some things, and put them into a handkerchief, that she took off her head. I was going to my mother's stall; I stopped, and looked at them.
